A 49-year-old man died after he was attacked by bees at his home in Kwanza, Trans Nzoia County yesterday.  Titus Wanyonyi Okodoi was at his home with relatives when bees attacked the residence, forcing them to flee.  Justus Wamalwa, a neighbour, told the police that Okodoi was discovered unconscious on the roadside and rushed to a nearby clinic where he died.  Area OCPD Joseph Mboya confirmed the incident. The body was taken to the Kitale County morgue.    Animal numbers tumble as fences block migration corridors  Uproar after church ploughs, plants maize on school playground  Women go against tradition, venture into honey business  Police on the spot after suspect found dead   Morning Express Sports Chat 9th May 2016 Trans Nzoia Sports Association  Mwanamke Ngangari: Seneta mteule Bi. Zipporah Kittony  CORD leader Raila Odinga hits out at DP Ruto for using Harambees to woo Western region into Jubilee By Weldon Kipkemoi | 6 hours ago By Patrick Beja | 1 day ago By Weldon Kipkemoi | 1 day ago By Philip Mwakio | 1 day ago Uhuru unveils major plans for Nyanza ahead of visit